# HTB Certified Penetration Testing Specialist (CPTS) ‚Äì Complete Preparation & Success Guide

https://www.linkedin.com/posts/professor-ankush-75b645321_cybersecurity-penetrationtesting-redteaming-activity-7416563160465293312-PfiE

This repository is my personal collection of notes, strategies, resources, and especially reporting guidance for passing the **Hack The Box Certified Penetration Testing Specialist (HTB CPTS)** certification in 2025‚Äì2026.

I passed CPTS after failing once (report got rejected even with 13/14 flags üòÖ), so everything here comes from real pain and lessons learned. This is **not** a walkthrough ‚Äî it's methodology, mindset, and especially why reporting is make-or-break.

**Last updated:** January 2026

## Why This Repo Exists

HTB CPTS is hands-down one of the toughest intermediate-level pentest certs right now.  
Many people say it's harder than OSCP in certain ways ‚Äî especially because:

- 10-day practical exam on a real enterprise-like AD environment
- You need ~12‚Äì14 flags (user + root/system)
- **You must submit a commercial-grade professional report**
- Even if you pwn everything, bad reporting = instant fail

I saw too many talented hackers fail just because their report looked like OSCP-style bullet points or lacked executive polish. That's why 40% of this guide is about reporting.

